items.abstract:
<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>
<jats:p>The mobility of the 110 nm-Fe<jats:sub>2</jats:sub>O<jats:sub>3</jats:sub> particles in a viscous sucrose solution depends on the concentration of the nanoparticles. When the average particle–particle nearest neighbor distance <<jats:italic>r</jats:italic>> is less than 250 nm, the particle interaction slows down their mobility. When <<jats:italic>r</jats:italic>> is more than 170 nm, the small mobility of nanoparticles does not depend on their concentration. The critical distance is approximately equal to 2<jats:italic>R<jats:sub>h</jats:sub></jats:italic> = 260 nm, where <jats:italic>R<jats:sub>h</jats:sub></jats:italic> is the hydrodynamic radius, determined by the dynamic light scattering (DLS) method.</jats:p>
